This paper discusses probabilistic formulations and their relevance to acquiring probabilistic knowledge from human experts. This topic falls under the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions belief networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses the process of acquiring knowledge, which could fall under the sub-category of social and information sciences (cs.SI).
